Inspiration 
The way people discover and evaluate recipes is broken. Home cooks scroll through endless blog posts padded with life stories, sift through inconsistent ratings on recipe sites, and have no reliable way to know if a recipe is actually worth making before committing time and ingredients. Existing platforms treat all recipes as equal — a five-star rating from someone who substituted half the ingredients sits alongside one from a seasoned cook who followed it precisely. We were inspired by Beli's approach to food reviews — personal, ranked, and social — and asked: what if we applied that same philosophy to recipes? Instead of building another recipe database, we set out to create a platform where your recipe ratings are contextualized, comparable, and connected to the people whose taste you actually trust. Our goal was to treat recipe discovery not as a search problem, but as a social trust network where the opinions that matter most come from people who cook like you and eat like you. 

What It Does 
Our system is a social recipe rating and discovery platform that lets users rank, review, and share recipes through a personalized, trust-driven feed. 
Rather than aggregating anonymous ratings, the platform operates as a taste-aware recommendation engine: 
- Lets users rate recipes on a normalized personal scale, so every rating is relative to their own cooking history 
- Builds a social graph of culinary trust — follow friends, home cooks, or creators whose palates and skill levels align with yours 
- Deduplicates recipes across sources, so the same dish from different blogs or platforms resolves to a single canonical entry Surfaces recommendations ranked by relevance to your taste profile, not by raw popularity 
- Tracks your personal cookbook — what you've made, what you loved, what you'd skip — as a living, searchable record Supports structured reviews capturing dimensions like difficulty, flavor accuracy, ingredient accessibility, and whether the recipe lives up to its photos 
This design ensures that discovery is personal, ratings are meaningful, and the best recipes rise to the top for the right audience. By anchoring recommendations in real social signal rather than anonymous averages, the platform becomes a reliable guide for deciding what to cook next.

